259
00:17:46,470 --> 00:17:51,250
I should've persuaded her to switch then.

260
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:53,160
Why didn't you?

261
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:57,820
I think it was a morning on a weekend.

262
00:17:58,740 --> 00:18:01,860
She said she wouldn't join Choeseon Korean,

263
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:05,540
and she came by to thank me for reviewing the contract.

264
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:09,650
She was humming, by the way.

265
00:18:09,650 --> 00:18:11,570
- Hye Jin was?
 - Yes, can you imagine?

266
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:12,870
No.

267
00:18:12,870 --> 00:18:15,010
I've never seen that.

268
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:18,540
The air around her felt softer.

269
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:23,820
I thought it was thanks to Mr. Lee. It was nice.

270
00:18:23,820 --> 00:18:26,510
She never had anyone to lean on.

271
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:30,440
She's the money-making machine at the academy,

272
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:33,900
and for the students, she's the grade-improving machine.

273
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:38,110
It seemed like she was finally able to breathe.

274
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:41,070
You were right.

275
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:46,040
I didn't know her old student could change her that much.

276
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:49,590
I don't know much about college preparation,

277
00:18:49,590 --> 00:18:52,700
but wasn't Mr. Lee right?

278
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:57,970
That doesn't mean he could make a profit that way, though.

279
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:01,910
You said you pitied her for being a money-making machine.

280
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:09,810
Someone at the legal training institute begged me to introduce Hye Jin to him.

281
00:19:09,810 --> 00:19:11,390
I should've set them up.

282
00:19:11,390 --> 00:19:14,890
Come on. What a cocky lady you are.

283
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:15,810
Me?

284
00:19:15,810 --> 00:19:19,370
You can't just force people to fall in love.

285
00:19:19,370 --> 00:19:23,690
How come you keep saying the right thing today?

286
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,990
Right, the battery.

287
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:22,910
Geez Louise!

288
00:20:22,910 --> 00:20:24,560
Did I wake you up?

289
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,720
You should've woken me up.

290
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:33,770
I wanted to see the sunrise.

291
00:20:33,770 --> 00:20:35,580
How pathetic.

292
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:37,710
You aren't pathetic.

293
00:20:37,710 --> 00:20:39,650
I should've set an alarm.

294
00:20:39,650 --> 00:20:41,790
It's okay, I said.

295
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:44,820
Let's get out.

296
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:49,720
I wanted to get out, but I waited so I didn't wake you up.

297
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:56,160
Seriously.

298
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:01,940
This feels surreal.

299
00:21:01,940 --> 00:21:06,070
I was walking on the rainy streets of Gangnam a few hours ago.

300
00:21:07,010 --> 00:21:09,470
This feels like a different world.

301
00:21:09,470 --> 00:21:11,510
- Aren't you glad you came?
 - Yes.

302
00:21:11,510 --> 00:21:14,480
I didn't know I could just come here like this.

303
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:23,650
I remember when we met in Namsan.

304
00:21:26,330 --> 00:21:30,370
I tried to change your mind, but it backfired.

305
00:21:30,370 --> 00:21:33,690
Backfired? Because of me?

306
00:21:33,690 --> 00:21:36,060
You threatened me, saying,

307
00:21:36,060 --> 00:21:39,410
"Is it okay if the academy knows you're doing this?"

308
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:45,800
I failed in Namsan, but your strategy worked.

309
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,440
If so...

310
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:53,060
Do what you want to do.

311
00:21:53,060 --> 00:21:55,730
Teach however you want.

312
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,690
I knew you'd be on board.

313
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:02,570
Although I would've kept pursuing it even if you weren't.

314
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:05,490
- You were planning to go rogue? 
 - No.

315
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:07,280
I would've kept persuading you.

316
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:09,660
No matter how many days it took.

317
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:12,030
I won't nag a lot.

318
00:22:13,980 --> 00:22:15,500
Be responsible.

319
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:17,720
The students' lives are at stake.

320
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:19,550
Of course.

321
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:22,900
Do you need help with anything?

322
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:25,580
You'd need a textbook first.

323
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:29,010
No, not stuff like that.

324
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:32,860
I want to do research and develop textbooks with you.

325
00:22:32,860 --> 00:22:36,100
I'm sure it'd be fun and amazing.

326
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:40,750
No.

327
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:46,450
It wasn't easy to achieve what I have, and I won't be that easily persuaded by a few words from you.

328
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:48,600
I definitely didn't build a sand castle.

329
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,360
I never said it was easy.

330
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:55,280
I'm suggesting we make it more fun and meaningful.

331
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:57,500
We can make the smartest students to come to us.

332
00:22:57,500 --> 00:23:01,300
Wake up. We aren't trying to raise students who'd be in textbooks.

333
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:03,470
Just send them to Seoul National Univ. or medical school.

334
00:23:03,470 --> 00:23:06,170
I already have truckloads of students like that.

335
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:09,880
But you have nothing. All you do is argue.

336
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,680
The beginning is always the hardest part.

337
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:15,480
So, stop wasting time trying to seduce me.

338
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,320
There are many more things to do.

339
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:22,620
♫  Oh the greatness I foresee  ♫

340
00:23:22,620 --> 00:23:27,430
♫  Just don't forget about me  ♫

341
00:23:30,340 --> 00:23:32,120
How pretty.

342
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:39,210
One. Be very careful when setting someone apart in an organization.

343
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:43,300
Once you do that, you don't know what they'll demand in the future.

344
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:44,820
Yes, that's true.

345
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:50,040
Two. Mr. Lee hasn't proven anything yet.

346
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:54,590
He did a great job with the demo lecture.

347
00:23:54,590 --> 00:23:57,700
Most of all, he started a Huiwon High class.

348
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:59,930
The demo was just a 10-minute lecture,

349
00:23:59,930 --> 00:24:04,380
and he had no chance of starting a Huiwon class without Seo Hye Jin.

350
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:07,100
Last ...

351
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:11,940
This is the biggest problem.

352
00:24:11,940 --> 00:24:14,680
Is it regarding the class focus?

353
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,370
Expand the understanding of humanity and the world

354
00:24:17,370 --> 00:24:19,810
by learning how to understand literature.

355
00:24:19,810 --> 00:24:24,970
What kind of utter nonsense is this?

356
00:24:24,970 --> 00:24:27,280
You're right.

357
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:31,190
If the academy allowed a classroom for a class like this,

358
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:35,130
other lecturers would feel disappointed. Don't you think?

359
00:24:35,130 --> 00:24:39,320
Many count on you and follow your lead, Manager Kim.

360
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:42,750
My goodness.

361
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:48,590
I always learn so much from you, Assistant Director.

362
00:24:49,210 --> 00:24:50,600
You're too generous.

363
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:55,450
I'll relay the message to Mr. Lee then.

364
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:01,200
I need to go meet someone.

365
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:03,680
Yes, of course.

366
00:25:11,260 --> 00:25:13,980
By the way, the class proposal...

367
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:17,190
Did Team Leader Seo approve it, too?

368
00:25:17,190 --> 00:25:19,210
I'm not sure.

369
00:25:20,780 --> 00:25:26,740
The Seo Hye Jin I know wouldn't have allowed that.

370
00:25:35,250 --> 00:25:37,620
Team Leader didn't get to see it.

371
00:25:37,620 --> 00:25:40,900
I came up with it on my own.

372
00:25:43,430 --> 00:25:45,290
I'll report to the Director directly.

373
00:25:45,290 --> 00:25:47,490
It's not that she thinks it's no good.

374
00:25:47,490 --> 00:25:50,410
She just thinks it's not the time yet.

375
00:25:50,410 --> 00:25:54,500
You need to listen to the higher-ups for now, okay?

376
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:59,190
Don't rush into things and get singled out.

377
00:25:59,190 --> 00:26:00,620
I'm not disappointed.

378
00:26:00,620 --> 00:26:03,250
I knew she wouldn't allow it immediately.

379
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:04,640
Yes.

380
00:26:09,050 --> 00:26:11,590
Yes, I know you tried your best.

381
00:26:11,590 --> 00:26:13,130
Not at all.

382
00:26:13,130 --> 00:26:16,170
I'll see you tonight. Okay.

383
00:26:22,620 --> 00:26:24,390
You scared me.

384
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:27,670
- Why?
 - I thought you disappeared.

385
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:32,340
We should leave now.

386
00:26:40,060 --> 00:26:41,610
Seo Hye Jin.

387
00:26:47,190 --> 00:26:48,770
What?

388
00:26:48,770 --> 00:26:52,180
If we leave now, this would be basically a work trip.

389
00:26:53,850 --> 00:26:55,250
You're right.

390
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:58,970
This is our first trip as a couple. We can do this much, right?

391
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:05,430
I thought you would've left notes.

392
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:11,950
This was neither homework nor an essay.

393
00:27:11,950 --> 00:27:13,950
You don't need my notes.

394
00:27:13,950 --> 00:27:15,340
Okay.

395
00:27:15,340 --> 00:27:17,120
But instead...

396
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:23,150
I wrote something at the end of each review.

397
00:27:23,150 --> 00:27:24,200
Pardon?

398
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:28,280
Your goal is to do well in exams no matter what.

399
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:33,660
Modern literature, poetry, classic literature, lyrics,

400
00:27:33,660 --> 00:27:35,810
and essays.

401
00:27:35,810 --> 00:27:38,300
I wrote about how I recommend reading it

402
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:42,110
and how I would've interpreted it if I were you.

403
00:27:42,870 --> 00:27:45,500
I wrote stuff like that.

404
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:49,570
Read it later. Don't read it here.

405
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,890
By the way, Mr. Pyo,

406
00:27:58,720 --> 00:28:03,410
I gave this to you yesterday. How did you already finish it...

407
00:28:04,380 --> 00:28:06,150
I stayed up all night.

408
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:09,290
Thank you.

409
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:13,160
Even so, It was enjoyable.

410
00:28:14,420 --> 00:28:17,290
You can leave. I'm busy.

411
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:34,740
I take back the offer.

412
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:38,180
What a shame.

413
00:28:39,370 --> 00:28:41,440
What will you do now?

414
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:45,090
You've been enduring pain for eight years and seven months.

415
00:28:45,090 --> 00:28:47,940
Do you want to wait a few more months?

416
00:28:47,940 --> 00:28:50,570
Only the order was changed.

417
00:28:50,570 --> 00:28:53,940
Instead of making a move after striking Seo Hye Jin's neck,

418
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:57,110
I can aim for her neck from the outside.

419
00:28:57,110 --> 00:29:00,610
Korean department. Lee Myeong Jun, Nam Cheong Mi, and Kim Chae Yun.

420
00:29:00,610 --> 00:29:02,590
English department. Yun Ji Seok, Jang Il Do,

421
00:29:02,590 --> 00:29:05,220
Cheon Yi Chang, Kang Gi Ho, and Lee Geum Hyang.

422
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:07,660
Social studies. Min Hui Ju.

423
00:29:07,660 --> 00:29:11,140
Lastly, there's Lee Jun Ho of the Korean department.

424
00:29:11,140 --> 00:29:16,420
But since he's on Seo Hye Jin's side, he's an exception.

425
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:17,960
Is that pretty much it?

426
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:21,620
The ones you'd be putting in your ark.

427
00:29:26,510 --> 00:29:31,610
Will Nam Cheong Mi or Kim Chae Yun take those files?

428
00:29:31,610 --> 00:29:33,530
Didn't I tell you?

429
00:29:33,530 --> 00:29:37,000
In the long run, we're competitors, too.

430
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,140
How could I disclose something like that?

431
00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:42,030
Don't think of me as your competition.

432
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:46,690
Try using me in a more constructive way.

433
00:29:46,690 --> 00:29:51,110
If you bring those teachers to my academy,

434
00:29:51,110 --> 00:29:54,400
I'll do a lot for you in return.

435
00:29:54,400 --> 00:30:00,980
What would Choeseon Korean do with the English and social studies teachers?

436
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:02,870
I should embrace all of them.

437
00:30:02,870 --> 00:30:06,490
It will be Choeseon Academy, not Choeseon Korean.

438
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:16,680
But before that, how about you add another person to the ark?

439
00:30:18,170 --> 00:30:21,710
Do you mean Seo Hye Jin?

440
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:27,230
Looks like I still can't get over her.

441
00:30:27,230 --> 00:30:33,380
Your goal was to separate Seo Hye Jin from Director Kim, anyway.

442
00:30:33,380 --> 00:30:35,560
Wouldn't that be good?

443
00:30:46,420 --> 00:30:48,260
Why? What is it?

444
00:30:48,260 --> 00:30:50,620
I have to see someone.

445
00:30:50,620 --> 00:30:53,690
You need to do something while I'm meeting this person.

446
00:30:53,690 --> 00:30:55,340
It's homework.

447
00:30:55,340 --> 00:30:57,860
After you drop me off,

448
00:30:57,860 --> 00:31:01,930
go straight to your parents' house. Sleep there tonight.

449
00:31:01,930 --> 00:31:03,150
I don't want to.

450
00:31:03,150 --> 00:31:06,140
It's homework, I said. You have no choice.

451
00:31:06,140 --> 00:31:08,200
Why do I have to do that?

452
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:12,210
Tell your parents what you think calmly and nicely.

453
00:31:12,210 --> 00:31:14,730
Make them feel better, too.

454
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:18,960
I can manage that myself.

455
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:25,300
I want my boyfriend to be a good person.

456
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:28,670
I'm tall, handsome, and rich. Doesn't that make me a good one?

457
00:31:28,670 --> 00:31:34,440
You said you'd teach the students how to read and enjoy literature properly.

458
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,840
What does that have to do with me being a good boyfriend?

459
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:39,760
Imagine a money-obsessed terrible son teaching the meaning of literature

460
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:41,990
and the author's interiority.

461
00:31:41,990 --> 00:31:44,140
Wouldn't that be absurd?

462
00:31:48,060 --> 00:31:50,010
You'll do the homework, right?

463
00:31:56,660 --> 00:32:00,730
Why does my girlfriend have to be a teacher?

464
00:32:32,980 --> 00:32:34,650
Yes.

465
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,480
Welcome, Team Leader Seo.

466
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:46,740
- Am I late?
 - No, I just got here, too.

467
00:32:46,740 --> 00:32:48,940
I'm sorry to make you come a long way.

468
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:50,380
There was traffic, right?

469
00:32:50,380 --> 00:32:53,090
No, I took the subway to avoid it.

470
00:32:53,090 --> 00:32:55,410
As I expected you are thorough.

471
00:32:55,410 --> 00:32:57,430
- Let's sit.
 - Okay.

472
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:03,990
I said we'd order food later. That's okay, right?

473
00:33:03,990 --> 00:33:05,510
Yes.

474
00:33:10,050 --> 00:33:13,600
I should do this more often. But it's not easy.

475
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:18,750
The teachers are so busy, and you're all competitors.

476
00:33:18,750 --> 00:33:21,130
It's hard to just hang out causally, too.

477
00:33:21,130 --> 00:33:22,660
Since it'd create rumors.

478
00:33:22,660 --> 00:33:26,650
You know how jealous everyone gets.

479
00:33:26,650 --> 00:33:29,610
So, I was surprised that you wanted to see me.

480
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:39,580
Not only that, we're meeting far away from the academy so openly and suspiciously, right?

481
00:33:40,940 --> 00:33:45,500
Since you must've figured out everything already,

482
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:47,560
mo need to beat around the bush, right?

483
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:48,940
Yes.

484
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:52,830
I'm preparing for retirement.

485
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:59,390
I thought you could handle another decade easily.

486
00:34:00,150 --> 00:34:02,930
I can't.

487
00:34:02,930 --> 00:34:08,400
I used to know all the students' names, but I can't do that anymore.

488
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:13,690
And it's not like I've done this forever

489
00:34:13,690 --> 00:34:16,930
like Director Choi, either.

490
00:34:16,930 --> 00:34:18,950
Does Director Kim know, too?

491
00:34:18,950 --> 00:34:20,590
Not yet.

492
00:34:21,410 --> 00:34:23,520
But interestingly,

493
00:34:26,570 --> 00:34:29,140
I received my retirement pay already.

494
00:34:30,540 --> 00:34:32,810
What do you mean by that?

495
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:41,510
What is that?

496
00:34:41,510 --> 00:34:45,170
The entire class material of yours.

497
00:34:45,170 --> 00:34:47,640
Including the pop quizzes.

498
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:07,100
Well, who...

499
00:35:07,100 --> 00:35:09,370
- How...
 - That's not important right now.

500
00:35:09,370 --> 00:35:13,080
What's important is that it's in my possession.

501
00:35:13,080 --> 00:35:14,680
Take it with you.

502
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:18,430
You need to confirm if I'm bluffing or not.

503
00:35:18,430 --> 00:35:21,400
You're proudly telling me you made copies, too?

504
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:24,180
I don't just have copies.

505
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:26,990
You must have other ideas, too.

506
00:35:26,990 --> 00:35:33,000
You aren't as shocked as I thought you'd be about the USB drive.

507
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:35,110
Did you know, by chance?

508
00:35:38,670 --> 00:35:41,210
I wonder who tipped you off.

509
00:35:42,030 --> 00:35:44,180
Does that matter?

510
00:35:46,860 --> 00:35:50,240
No. The possible candidates would be

511
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:52,510
the one who gave me these files

512
00:35:52,510 --> 00:35:56,580
and the one who wanted them badly. It's those two.

513
00:35:56,580 --> 00:35:59,770
What's important is that no one can use them.

514
00:35:59,770 --> 00:36:04,140
Shall we think about how we could make the most out of

515
00:36:04,140 --> 00:36:09,430
the work you created with blood, sweat, and tears?

516
00:36:23,930 --> 00:36:25,650
I...

517
00:36:27,590 --> 00:36:30,680
should leave the academy with you.

518
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:36,790
Otherwise, these files will be given to someone else.

519
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,350
Let's eat.

520
00:36:40,350 --> 00:36:43,600
I'm hungry since I didn't have a proper lunch.

521
00:36:44,690 --> 00:36:47,070
I hope you respect it.

522
00:36:47,740 --> 00:36:49,440
I will.

523
